This is a firebreath NPAPI plugin project

Install Dependencies
====================
* Download and extract firebreath
   currently the only branch of firebreath that will function is taxilians branch which removes GUI requirements and negates the need for libgtk2.0-dev; the branch is here: https://github.com/taxilian/FireBreath.git
* extract firebreath somewhere outside the gpgAuth src tree
* Install cmake, and libgpgme11-dev (Debian: apt-get install cmake libgpgme11-dev)


Prep Build Environment
======================
* Create a 'projects' folder under the firebreath root
* Symlink the gpgAuthPlugin directory to /path/to/firebreath/projects/gpgAuthPlugin
* cd /path/to/firebreath
* `./prepmake.sh`


Build gpgAuth Plugin
====================
* cd /path/to/firebreath/build
* `make`


Build Library Only
==================
* cd to /path/to/firebreath/projects/gpgAuthPlugin and execute:
* `make`


Load the Plugin in Chrome
=========================
* cd /path/to/gpgauth/gpgauth-chrome/plugin/linux/i386
* ln -s /path/to/firebreath/build/bin/gpgAuthPlugin/npgpgAuthPlugin.so .
* Go into Chrome and navigate to chrome:extensions
* Switch to developer mode
* Click 'Load unpacked extension'
* Navigate to /path/to/gpgauth/gpgauth-chrome and click 'ok'

The plugin should be loaded now.
Nagivate to http://gpgauth.org/tests/head_test.php
=======

Compiling in WINDOWS
==========================
(if you got past the title, hold on... what a pain in the ass)

Windows 32 or 64bit building instructions -

download tdm-gcc:

http://sourceforge.net/projects/tdm-gcc/files/TDM-GCC%20Installer/tdm-gcc-4.5.0.exe/download

- or -

http://iweb.dl.sourceforge.net/project/tdm-gcc/TDM-GCC%20Installer/tdm-gcc-4.5.0.exe

download cmake: http://www.cmake.org/files/v2.8/cmake-2.8.1-win32-x86.exe

download MSYS: ftp://ftp.gnupg.org/gcrypt/gpgme/gpgme-1.1.8.tar.bz2

download gpg-error, libassusan and gpgme from www.gnugpg.org

--- Compile GnuPG ---
Extract gnupg source files to C:\mysys\home\<USER>\gnupg

Open Start, Program Files, MSYS, cd to ~/gnupg

(starting with libassusan, then gpg-error, then gpgme)
for each directory, run './configure && make && make install'
This compiles and installs the needed gpgme libraries into your MSYS installation (by defualt, c:\msys\1.0\usr\, NOT your windows PC..




--- Compile gpgauth lib ---
g++ -Wall -I c:\msys\1.0\usr\include -L c:\msys\1.0\local\lib -lgpg-error -lgpgme -o gpgauth.exe gpgauth.cpp

